<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Akanthomyces" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Akanthomyces novoguineensis" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="novoguineensis">Akanthomyces novoguineensis</taxonomicName>
≡ 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Akanthomyces" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Akanthomyces novoguineensis" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="novoguineensis">Akanthomyces novoguineensis</taxonomicName>
Samson &amp; B.L. Brady, Trans. Br. mycol. Soc. 79: 571 (1982).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia novoguineensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="novoguineensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Hevansia novoguineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Samson &amp; B.L. Brady) Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, IMA Fungus 8: 349 (2017).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Emended generic description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
(modified from 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5598/imafungus.2017.08.02.08" author="Kepler, RM" journalOrPublisher="IMA Fungus" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="335 - 353" refId="B21" refString="Kepler, RM, Luangsa-ard, JJ, Hywel-Jones, NL, Quandt, CA, Sung, GH, Rehner, SA, Aime, MC, Henkel, TW, Sanjuan, T, Zare, R, Chen, M, Li, Z, Rossman, AY, Spatafora, JW, Shrestha, B, 2017. A phylogenetically-based nomenclature for Cordycipitaceae (Hypocreales). IMA Fungus 8 (2): 335 - 353, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5598/imafungus.2017.08.02.08" title="A phylogenetically-based nomenclature for Cordycipitaceae (Hypocreales)." url="https://doi.org/10.5598/imafungus.2017.08.02.08" volume="8" year="2017">Kepler et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName genus="Circumscription" lsidName="Circumscription" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Circumscription</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: The sexual morph characteristics in genus are emended, based on three species 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. minuta" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. nelumboides" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nelumboides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. nelumboides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. novoguineensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novoguineensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. novoguineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
producing sexual morph as members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, in Kepler, Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones, Quandt, Sung, Rehner, Aime, Henkel, Sanjuan, Zare, Chen, Li, Rossman, Spatafora, Shrestha, IMA Fungus 8: 348" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Hevansia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lineage in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. RAxML tree of Hevansia, Jenniferia, Parahevasia, Polystromomyces and related genera in the Cordycipitaceae from a combined ITS, LSU, tef 1, rpb 1 and rpb 2 dataset. Numbers at the major nodes represent Maximum Likelihood Bootstrap (MLB) and Bayesian Posterior Probabilities (BPP). Bold lines in the tree represent 100 % of MLB and 1.00 of BPP. Symbols on the right-hand side correspond to the types of ascospore morphologies found in each genus that are observed in natural specimens of Cordycipitaceae described in Fig. 2." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.91.83091.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719474" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">1</figureCitation>
. Sexual morph: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Stromata</emphasis>
arising from dorsal abdomen, stipe 1-10 mm, fertile part at the terminal of stipe, ca. 1-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, white to cream. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Perithecia</emphasis>
immersed, narrowly ovoid. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Asci</emphasis>
cylindrical with thickened caps, 8-spored, ascospores hyaline, filiform, whole or disarticulating into part-spores. Asexual morph: 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="Synnemata" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Synnemata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Synnemata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
erect, simple or branched, solitary to numerous, cylindrical to clavate, mycelium covering host, white, cream to ash-grey or brownish-white. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Phialides</emphasis>
in a monolayer, sparsely scattered or crowded, on mycelium or on a basal cell, smooth-walled, cylindrical, globose, obovoid, with distinct necks. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Conidia</emphasis>
one-celled, smooth-walled, hyaline, occasionally in a short chain, clavate, cylindrical, fusiform to narrowly obclavate. Colony on PDA white, reverse cream, orange to pale red. Some species produce pale red pigment diffusing in the medium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
Two specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. arachnophila" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arachnophila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. arachnophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NHJ 2465, NHJ 2633) were described by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0953-7562(96)80214-0" author="Hywel-Jones, NL" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="1065 - 1070" refId="B18" refString="Hywel-Jones, NL, 1996. Akanthomyces on spiders in Thailand. Mycological Research 100 (9): 1065 - 1070, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/S0953-7562(96)80214-0" title="Akanthomyces on spiders in Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0953-7562(96)80214-0" volume="100" year="1996">Hywel-Jones (1996)</bibRefCitation>
. While the type strain of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. websteri" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="websteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. websteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NHJ 2661) and living cultures are unavailable, available sequences of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. arachnophila" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arachnophila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. arachnophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and two strains of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. websteri" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="websteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. websteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(BCC 23860, BCC 36541) were retrieved from the GenBank nucleotide database and used in this study. The phylogenetic tree revealed that 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. arachnophila" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arachnophila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. arachnophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. websteri" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="websteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. websteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(BCC 23860, BCC 36541) belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, in Kepler, Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones, Quandt, Sung, Rehner, Aime, Henkel, Sanjuan, Zare, Chen, Li, Rossman, Spatafora, Shrestha, IMA Fungus 8: 348" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Hevansia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. RAxML tree of Hevansia, Jenniferia, Parahevasia, Polystromomyces and related genera in the Cordycipitaceae from a combined ITS, LSU, tef 1, rpb 1 and rpb 2 dataset. Numbers at the major nodes represent Maximum Likelihood Bootstrap (MLB) and Bayesian Posterior Probabilities (BPP). Bold lines in the tree represent 100 % of MLB and 1.00 of BPP. Symbols on the right-hand side correspond to the types of ascospore morphologies found in each genus that are observed in natural specimens of Cordycipitaceae described in Fig. 2." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.91.83091.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719474" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">1</figureCitation>
). The two strains of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. websteri" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="websteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. websteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(BCC 23860, BCC 36541) were not designated as type, nor as neotype. These strains (BCC 23860, BCC 36541) were thus named as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, IMA Fungus 8: 349" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Hywel-Jones" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia websteri" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="websteri">Hevansia cf. websteri</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, IMA Fungus 8: 349" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="B. Huang, S. B. Wang, M. Z. Fan &amp; Z. Z. Li" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia longispora" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="longispora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Hevansia longispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. ovalongata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovalongata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. ovalongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not included in the phylogenetic study because multi-locus sequence data are unavailable. To better resolve the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, in Kepler, Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones, Quandt, Sung, Rehner, Aime, Henkel, Sanjuan, Zare, Chen, Li, Rossman, Spatafora, Shrestha, IMA Fungus 8: 348" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Hevansia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. longispora" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. longispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. ovalongata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovalongata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. ovalongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. websteri" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="websteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. websteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be recollected from the locality and designated as neotypes and studied for their phylogenetic affinity to other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones &amp; Spatafora, in Kepler, Luangsa-ard, Hywel-Jones, Quandt, Sung, Rehner, Aime, Henkel, Sanjuan, Zare, Chen, Li, Rossman, Spatafora, Shrestha, IMA Fungus 8: 348" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Hevansia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hevansia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Hevansia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in the future. However, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. longispora" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. longispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. ovalongata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovalongata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">H. ovalongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. websteri" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="websteri">
